50|$|The Pulitzer Center on Crisis Reporting is an American {{news media}} {{organization}} established in 2006 that sponsors independent reporting on global issues that other media outlets are less willing {{or able to}} undertake on their own. The Center's goal is to raise the standard of coverage of international <b>systemic</b> <b>crises,</b> and to do so in a way that engages both the broad public and government policy-makers. The organization is based in Washington, D.C.|$|R
